.TH UTILITYKIT 1 "July 2026" "UtilityKit v5.10.6" "UtilityKit Tools"
.SH NAME
utility-env_manager \- Manage `.env` profiles, validate environment file syntax, compare active keys against an example file, and encrypt or decrypt secret files using `gpg` or `openssl`.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B utility env_manager
[\fIoptions\fP]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Manage `.env` profiles, validate environment file syntax, compare active keys against an example file, and encrypt or decrypt secret files using `gpg` or `openssl`.
.SH FEATURES
.PP
.IP \(bu 4
\fBProfile switching\fP — copy any \fC.env.<profile>\fP file over your active \fC.env\fP in one step
.IP \(bu 4
\fBSyntax validation\fP — scan an env file line by line and flag any malformed \fCkey=value\fP entries
.IP \(bu 4
\fBKey comparison\fP — diff your active \fC.env\fP against \fC.env.example\fP to find missing or extra keys
.IP \(bu 4
\fBEncryption\fP — encrypt secret files using \fCgpg -c\fP (preferred) or \fCopenssl aes-256-cbc\fP fallback
.IP \(bu 4
\fBDecryption\fP — decrypt \fC.gpg\fP or \fC.enc\fP files back to plaintext
.IP \(bu 4
\fBInteractive mode\fP — running the tool without arguments launches a guided menu
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH USAGE
.PP
.EX
bash _env_manager/_env_manager.sh --dir . --compare

bash _env_manager/_env_manager.sh --dir . --validate

bash _env_manager/_env_manager.sh --validate .env.production

bash _env_manager/_env_manager.sh --dir . --profile staging --apply

bash _env_manager/_env_manager.sh --dir . --profile staging

bash _env_manager/_env_manager.sh --encrypt .env.production

bash _env_manager/_env_manager.sh --decrypt .env.production.gpg

bash _env_manager/_env_manager.sh
.EE
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH OPTIONS
.PP
Option   |   Description
\fC--dir DIR\fP   |   Project directory containing \fC.env\fP files (default: \fC.\fP)
\fC--profile NAME\fP   |   Profile name to inspect or switch to (e.g. \fClocal\fP, \fCstaging\fP, \fCproduction\fP)
\fC--apply\fP   |   Actually copy the selected profile to \fC.env\fP (default is dry-run)
\fC--compare\fP   |   Compare active \fC.env\fP keys against \fC.env.example\fP
\fC--validate [FILE]\fP   |   Validate syntax of FILE, or active \fC.env\fP if no file given
\fC--encrypt FILE\fP   |   Encrypt FILE using \fCgpg\fP or \fCopenssl\fP
\fC--decrypt FILE\fP   |   Decrypt a \fC.gpg\fP or \fC.enc\fP file
\fC--active FILE\fP   |   Override the active env filename (default: \fC.env\fP)
\fC--example FILE\fP   |   Override the example env filename (default: \fC.env.example\fP)
\fC-h, --help\fP   |   Show usage
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH PROFILE CONVENTIONS
.PP
The tool expects profile files to follow the \fC.env.<name>\fP naming convention inside the project directory:
.PP
.EX
project/
├── .env               ← active file (loaded by your app)
├── .env.example       ← reference file checked in to version control
├── .env.local         ← local development overrides
├── .env.staging       ← staging environment values
└── .env.production    ← production values (encrypt before committing)
.EE
.PP
Switching to a profile with \fC--apply\fP copies the selected file over \fC.env\fP. Without \fC--apply\fP the tool performs a dry-run and shows what would happen.
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH ENCRYPTION BACKENDS
.PP
The tool tries \fCgpg\fP first and falls back to \fCopenssl\fP if \fCgpg\fP is not available:
.PP
.IP \(bu 4
\fCgpg -c\fP produces a \fC.gpg\fP file using symmetric passphrase encryption
.IP \(bu 4
\fCopenssl enc -aes-256-cbc -pbkdf2\fP produces a \fC.enc\fP file
.PP
Decryption automatically detects the file extension and uses the matching backend.
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH EXIT CODES
.PP
Code   |   Meaning
\fC0\fP   |   Success
\fC1\fP   |   Missing file, invalid profile, or encryption/decryption failure
